Package gw.api.databuilder

Class ClaimIndicatorTriggerBuilder

java.lang.Object
gw.api.databuilder.DataBuilder<ClaimIndicatorTrigger,ClaimIndicatorTriggerBuilder>
gw.api.databuilder.CCDataBuilder<ClaimIndicatorTrigger,ClaimIndicatorTriggerBuilder>
gw.api.databuilder.ClaimIndicatorTriggerBuilder
All Implemented Interfaces:
DelegateDataBuilder<ClaimIndicatorTrigger>, ValueGenerator<ClaimIndicatorTrigger>
public class ClaimIndicatorTriggerBuilder extends CCDataBuilder<ClaimIndicatorTrigger,ClaimIndicatorTriggerBuilder>
A data builder for a ClaimIndicatorTrigger, which is used to invoke special handling for a claim when one of its Claim Indicators changes.
Author:
jdonahue

  • Constructor Details

    • ClaimIndicatorTriggerBuilder

      public ClaimIndicatorTriggerBuilder()
      The default constructor a ClaimIndicatorTriggerBuilder. This builder has no value set for either the ClaimIndicator on which to trigger or the triggering value.

  • Method Details

    • withClaimIndicator

      public ClaimIndicatorTriggerBuilder withClaimIndicator(ClaimIndicator claimIndicator)
      Sets the type of ClaimIndicator that this trigger will test when deciding whether to fire.
      Parameters:
      claimIndicator - a member of the ClaimIndicatorIntSubtype typelist indicating the subtype of ClaimIndicator to test.
      Returns:
      ClaimIndicatorTriggerBuilder with the ClaimIndicator set

    • withTriggeringValue

      public ClaimIndicatorTriggerBuilder withTriggeringValue(boolean valueToTriggerOn)
      Sets the value that this trigger will test for when deciding whether to fire.
      Parameters:
      valueToTriggerOn - if TRUE, the constructed trigger will test for whether the indicator has been turned on, else it will test for whether the indicator has been turned off.
      Returns:
      ClaimIndicatorTriggerBuilder with the TriggeringValue set

    • triggerWhenOn

      public ClaimIndicatorTriggerBuilder triggerWhenOn()
      Configures this builder to produce a ClaimIndicatorTrigger that only triggers when the Indicator is turned on.
      Returns:
      ClaimIndicatorTriggerBuilder with TriggeringValue set to TRUE

    • triggerWhenOff

      public ClaimIndicatorTriggerBuilder triggerWhenOff()
      Configures this builder to produce a ClaimIndicatorTrigger that only triggers when the Indicator is turned off.
      Returns:
      ClaimIndicatorTriggerBuilder with TriggeringValue set to FALSE
